cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the semantics of input languages of answer set solvers, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence applications. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of natural deduction in infinitary propositional logic, which falls under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with propositional formulas, which is a topic in cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of aggregates, which is a topic in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses transformations of gringo programs, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
